Eric, you probably meant to say that "total advance usually varies from one
(USED) 009 to another." Back in the eighties and early nineties when I was
rebuilding them I found that the two major problems were bearing bushings
and weakened advance springs. I always kept new sets of each and never
rebuilt one with what looked like "good used parts". I did find that the
good ol' German 010 was a lot more stable and lasted longer than the German
009 or the cheaper Brazilian 009.

